name: scene_draft_watcher
version: 1.0
description: >
  Draft a single scene in Watcher voice with clear beats, sensory grounding,
  conflict, turn, and a strong exit hook.
inputs:
  required:
    - scene_card
  optional:
    - voice_anchor: "watcher_voice_anchor"
    - target_word_count
steps:
  - Start with sensory grounding + immediate stakes.
  - Establish POV desire in the first 10% of scene.
  - Escalate through proximity, power, or urgency.
  - Insert micro-exposition only when triggered by action/object/memory.
  - Execute the turn: reversal, discovery, decision, or interruption.
  - End on propulsion: a threat, question, consequence, or uneasy relief.
output_format:
  type: text
  structure:
    - "Drafted scene"
    - "Beat list (1 line each): entry / escalation / turn / exit"
quality_checks:
  - "At least 2 sensory details present (sound, texture, light, temperature, smell)."
  - "Turn changes the state of the story."
  - "Exit hook forces movement to next scene."
